com21HcxVoice.name: com21HcxVoice
com21HcxVoice.contactinfo: Network Management Postal: Paul Gordon Com21, Inc. 750 Tasman Drive Milpitas, California 95035 USA Tel: +1 408 953 9100 Fax: +1 408 953 9299 E-mail: pgordon@com21.com
com21HcxVoice.description: This is the Com21 ComController Oc3 MIB module. COM21 Part# 005-0025-00

hcxConfiguredVoiceChannels.name: hcxConfiguredVoiceChannels
hcxConfiguredVoiceChannels.description: Defines the number of Voice Channels currently configured on the system.

hcxActiveVoiceChannels.name: hcxActiveVoiceChannels
hcxActiveVoiceChannels.description: Defines the number of Voice Channels that are currently active on the system.

hcxVoiceChannelMode.name: hcxVoiceChannelMode
hcxVoiceChannelMode.description: Defines the type of compression scheme to be used for voice. Default is aLaw.

hcxVoiceOAMEnable.name: hcxVoiceOAMEnable
hcxVoiceOAMEnable.description: Defines whether OAM cells should be transmitted on voice VCC's when voice calls are idle. default: disable

hcxVoiceFEndEchoCancEnable.name: hcxVoiceFEndEchoCancEnable
hcxVoiceFEndEchoCancEnable.description: Defines whether Far End Echo Cancellation should be enabled or not. Default: disable

hcxVoiceRTTDelay.name: hcxVoiceRTTDelay
hcxVoiceRTTDelay.description: Defines the Round Trip Transit Delay in milliseconds. This should be configured if 'hcxVoiceFEndEchoCancEnable' is enabled. Default: 0

hcxVpnRxNum.name: hcxVpnRxNum
hcxVpnRxNum.description: Defines the Vpn Number. Used as Index.

hcxVpnRxEntryId.name: hcxVpnRxEntryId
hcxVpnRxEntryId.description: Defines the Rx Group Id. Used as Index.

hcxVpnRxRowStatus.name: hcxVpnRxRowStatus
hcxVpnRxRowStatus.description: Used to create an Instance of Rx Group Id for a given VPN. Deactive is not allowed.

hcxVpnRxMaxActiveCalls.name: hcxVpnRxMaxActiveCalls
hcxVpnRxMaxActiveCalls.description: Defines the maximum number of voice calls that should be allowed for this VPN on this Rx Group .

hcxVpnRxStatsNum.name: hcxVpnRxStatsNum
hcxVpnRxStatsNum.description: Defines the VPN value for which the stats are collected. Used as Index.

hcxVpnRxStatsEntryId.name: hcxVpnRxStatsEntryId
hcxVpnRxStatsEntryId.description: Defines the Rx Group Number for which the stats are collected. Used as Index.

hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsAllwd.name: hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsAllwd
hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of calls allowed in the given 15-min period for a ComPort on this Rx Group and on this VPN.

hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsBlkd.name: hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsBlkd
hcxVpnRxStatsCurrCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of calls blocked in the given 15-min period for a ComPort on this Rx Group and on this VPN.

hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsAllwd.name: hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsAllwd
hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of calls allowed in the previous 15-min period for a ComPort on this Rx Group and on this VPN.

hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsBlkd.name: hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsBlkd
hcxVpnRxStatsPrevCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of calls blocked in the previous 15-min period for a ComPort on this Rx Group and on this VPN.

hcxVpnRxStatsClear.name: hcxVpnRxStatsClear
hcxVpnRxStatsClear.description: This attribute is used to clear all call statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.

hcxStuVoiceChannelMacAddr.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelMacAddr
hcxStuVoiceChannelMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuVoiceChannelNum.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelNum
hcxStuVoiceChannelNum.description: Defines the voice channel on the Comport device used for Voice.

hcxStuVoiceChannelVpi.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelVpi
hcxStuVoiceChannelVpi.description: Defines the VPI to use to connect the Comport's voice channel to the external device on the OC3 wan port. The 'hcxStuVoiceChannelVpi', 'hcxStuVoiceChannelVci' combination should form a unique VCC for each entry in 'com21HcxStuVoiceChannelTable'. Default is 0

hcxStuVoiceChannelVci.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelVci
hcxStuVoiceChannelVci.description: Defines the VCI to use to connect the Comport's voice channel to the external device on the OC3 wan port. The 'hcxStuVoiceChannelVpi', 'hcxStuVoiceChannelVci' combination should form a unique VCC for each entry in 'com21HcxStuVoiceChannelTable'. Default is 0

hcxStuVoiceChannelPriStatus.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelPriStatus
hcxStuVoiceChannelPriStatus.description: Used to control Create, Activate/Deactivate, or Destroy a row. Activation/Deactivation of the row is not allowed if all writeable attributes do not have valid values.

hcxStuVoiceChannelState.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelState
hcxStuVoiceChannelState.description: Defines the current state of the port. voicePortActive indicates that the call is in progress

hcxStuVoiceChannelExtLpBk.name: hcxStuVoiceChannelExtLpBk
hcxStuVoiceChannelExtLpBk.description: If this attribute is enabled, the Oc3 Port will loopback all cells received on this VCC. The attribute cannot be enabled if voiceChannel is active, and if this attribute is enabled, voiceChannel will not be allowed to go active. default: disable.

hcxStuVoiceCallStatsMacAddr.name: hcxStuVoiceCallStatsMacAddr
hcxStuVoiceCallStatsMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuVoiceCallStatsNum.name: hcxStuVoiceCallStatsNum
hcxStuVoiceCallStatsNum.description: Defines the voice channel on the Comport device used for Voice.

hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsAllwd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsAllwd
hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of Incoming calls allowed in the given 15-min time period. Incoming calls are calls being placed to this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsAllwd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsAllwd
hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of Outgoing calls allowed in the given 15-min time period. Outgoing calls are calls being placed by this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsBlkd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsBlkd
hcxStuVoiceCallCurrInCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of Incoming calls blocked in the given 15-min time period. Incoming calls are calls being placed to this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsBlkd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsBlkd
hcxStuVoiceCallCurrOutCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of Outgoing calls blocked in the given 15-min time period. Outgoing calls are calls being placed by this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsAllwd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsAllwd
hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of Incoming calls allowed in the previous 15-min time period. Incoming calls are calls being placed to this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsAllwd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsAllwd
hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsAllwd.description: Defines the number of Outgoing calls blocked in the previous 15-min time period. Outgoing calls are calls being placed by this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsBlkd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsBlkd
hcxStuVoiceCallPrevInCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of Incoming calls blocked in the previous 15-min time period. Incoming calls are calls being placed to this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsBlkd.name: hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsBlkd
hcxStuVoiceCallPrevOutCallsBlkd.description: Defines the number of Outgoing calls blocked in the previous 15-min time period. Outgoing calls are calls being placed by this voice channel.

hcxStuVoiceCallStatsClear.name: hcxStuVoiceCallStatsClear
hcxStuVoiceCallStatsClear.description: This attribute is used to clear all the voice channel statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.
